An adventurer losing his way... 
Unheard of...
11:
*sigh* I landed myself in this trouble. 
I must pull myselfâ€”
24: Hi there, bunny... Where you going?
38:
Are... Are you a monster? *whimper* 
...Think I soiled my armor.
42: You are... quite nervous for your size.
45:
Do not be frightened. I am no 
monster... or rabbit. I am Light, 
a champion.
51:
I'm Walter. Would you mind telling 
me... how you became a champion?
54:
Not at all. But before that, will you not 
lead me to the Guild?
58:
Walter, thank you for bringing Light 
back to us.
62:
Yes... You saved me much time and 
trouble.
66:
It's, uh... no big deal. I bring lost kids 
back to the Guild more often than 
you'd think...
68:
The other soldiers tease me... for being
 a pineapple. You know, sweet on the 
inside, but tough and gnarly-looking 
on the outside?
72:
Yeah... I'll admit, the first time I saw 
you with Light, I thought you were 
trying to strong-arm him.
76:
Sorry... *sniff* Wish I hadn't been born 
with this face.
81:
You are not to blame for how you are 
treated. Forgive us. Alk spoke out of 
line.
84: Oh, no! There's nothing to forgive.
88:
So, uh... Light told me you're trying to 
send him home.
94:
Try not to spread it around town 
though. People might freak if they 
found out about the World Flipper.
97:
I won't. I was just wondering... if I could 
help.
101:
Oh. I mean, sure, we'd appreciate it, 
but... why?
104:
I heard about your adventures. They 
can get dangerous, and Light is so 
cute and small...
106:
But he's still out here, trying his best. 
Just *sniffle* being brave...
113:
I can't fight... and on bad days, I can 
go through three pairs of underpants. 
But I'm sturdy. You could use me as a 
shield...
117: I never asked for a guardian.
121:
But I am always seeking new 
comrades. Many of our fighters don't 
pay enough mind to defense. 
They could learn much from you.
134:
...I'll see Light safely back in Bunny 
Kingdom!
